transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_001
transcriptEntries.text: Good morning everyone. Let's get started with our daily standup. I'll go first quickly. Yesterday I finished the user story prioritization for next sprint, today I'm meeting with PM about the Q4 roadmap. No blockers. Jack, you're up.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_002
transcriptEntries.text: Sure, um, yesterday I was working on the authentication module, specifically the JWT implementation. Today I'm continuing with that, working on the token generation logic. No blockers.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_003
transcriptEntries.text: Great. How's the complexity looking? Is it tracking with your estimates?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_004
transcriptEntries.text: Yeah, so far it's looking good. I mean, JWT is pretty standard. I'm following some examples and documentation, so should be fine.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_005
transcriptEntries.text: That's great Jack. Just remember if you hit any architectural questions, especially around token refresh patterns, feel free to ping me. I've implemented that a few times before.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_006
transcriptEntries.text: Cool, thanks Mike. I'll let you know if I need anything.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_008
transcriptEntries.text: Thanks Sarah. Yesterday I finished up the email validation component, today I'm starting on OAuth integration with third-party providers. I might need some guidance on the OAuth flow, actually. Jack, since you're working on auth stuff, could we sync up later?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_009
transcriptEntries.text: Um, yeah, sure. I'm still getting up to speed on some of the OAuth stuff myself, but we can figure it out together.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_010
transcriptEntries.text: I can jump in here too. Yesterday I wrapped up the user profile endpoints, today I'm working on the admin dashboard queries. No blockers. And I've done OAuth integrations before, so if you need help Lisa, I'm available too.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_011
transcriptEntries.text: And for me, yesterday I completed the database migrations for the new user fields, today I'm optimizing some of the slow queries we identified last week. One small blocker - I need the final auth table schema before I can finish the user session optimizations.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_012
transcriptEntries.text: Good point Alex. Jack, can you share the auth schema design by end of week? That'll help Alex move forward.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_013
transcriptEntries.text: Yeah, absolutely. I should have that ready by Thursday or Friday latest.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_014
transcriptEntries.text: Perfect. Alright everyone, that's our standup. Remember we have sprint planning on Monday, and the architecture review tomorrow at 10. Have a great day!

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-standup-identity-platform-oct01/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_015
transcriptEntries.text: Thanks Sarah. See you all later. Bye everyone.
